### Cache invalidation notes

- Mutation endpoints in `projects`, `chapters`, `glossary`, `cover/metadata`, and `publish` flows invalidate Redis-backed caches for:
  - public metadata entities (`/api/public/entities`) after admin create,
  - user project views (`/api/projects`, `/api/projects/:id`, summaries),
  - publication pages (`/api/publications/*`) when relevant,
  - user reading/token aggregates where relevant.
- This prevents stale UI after successful write operations.

